					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/accelerando" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1599414); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1599414&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226603" alt="Accelerando" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1599414)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/accelerando" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1599414); return false;" >Accelerando</a></span> <span class="odate time_1530130920 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Jun 2018 20:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3852669">
									

<p>I doubt Leave Earth will be as strong as No Now. And nothing against Fantano, but I'm pretty sure No Now was the last interesting album I found through him.</p>
<p>Death Grips are alright for letting off steam, but I don't listen to them regularly. I do think Flatlander is consistently great on every album I hear, maybe it's why I like Government Plates the most.</p>

							</div>

								
					
